  "question_id": "cdae9304-0598-4664-875b-199df1ec6094",
  "short_text": "Print the Characters",
  "content": "Write a program that reads a string and prints each character of the given string on a new line.\n\n---\n\n#### Input\n\nThe input will be a single line containing a string.\n\n---\n\n#### Output\n\nThe output should be `N` lines, with each line containing a string that is one of the characters of the given string. Here, `N` is the length of the given string.\n\n---\n\n#### Explanation\n\nFor example, if the given string is **shine**,\n\n- The length of the given string is **5**.\n- Each character of the string should be printed on a new line.\n\nThe output should be,\n\n```\ns\nh\ni\nn\ne\n```\n",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "32d2737d-165f-4901-81cd-b2b8b71ecce6",
      "code_content": "string = input()\n\nindex = 0\nlength = len(string)\n\nwhile index < length:\n    character = string[index]\n    print(character)\n    index = index + 1",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
  ],
